metadata.name: Dusty Bagan
metadata.description:
A herd of cattle returning from pasture at the end of long dusty day in Bagan, Myanmar.
This was taken from Pyathatgyi temple during sunset in 14th Jan 2014 and published in National Geographic Travel Magazine online. 
Nowadays it becomes a very rare scene to be seen in Bagan and it is also restricted for photographers to go up to the high level of the ancient temples in Bagan to take photographs.
